		"name": "MDD API",
		"description": "# MDD (Monde de D√©v) - REST API\n\n## Overview\nThis is the complete API documentation for the MDD social network application. The API allows developers to share articles, subscribe to topics, and engage in discussions.\n\n## Authentication\nThis API uses **HTTP-only cookies** for authentication, providing enhanced security against XSS attacks.\n\n### How it works:\n1. Login via `POST /api/auth/login` - Receives `access_token` and `refresh_token` cookies\n2. Cookies are automatically sent with subsequent requests\n3. Access tokens expire after 1 hour\n4. Use `POST /api/auth/refresh` to renew tokens\n5. Logout via `POST /api/auth/logout` clears all cookies\n\n‚ö†Ô∏è **Important**: Make sure \"Send cookies\" is enabled in Postman settings for authenticated requests.\n\n## Base URL\n```\nhttp://localhost:8080/api\n```\n\n## Response Formats\nAll responses are in JSON format.\n\n### Success Response Example:\n```json\n{\n  \"message\": \"Operation successful\"\n}\n```\n\n### Error Response Example:\n```json\n{\n  \"message\": \"Error description\"\n}\n```\n\n## Endpoints Overview\n\n### üîê Authentication\n- Register new user\n- Login with username or email\n- Refresh access token\n- Logout\n\n### üë§ User Management\n- Get current user profile\n- Update user information\n\n### üìö Topics\n- Browse all available topics\n- Get user subscribed topics\n- Subscribe/unsubscribe to topics\n\n### üì∞ Feed\n- Get personalized feed from subscribed topics\n- Pagination and sorting support\n\n### üìù Posts\n- View post details\n- Create new posts\n- Read and add comments\n\n---\n\n**Version:** 1.0.0  \n**Author:** C√©cile UMECKER",
